of our days we go to sleep,

00:17:58.800 --> 00:18:02.180 align:middle line:84%
we can still remember
that time of waking up.

00:18:02.180 --> 00:18:04.310 align:middle line:84%
Where suddenly, I
mean sensorally,

00:18:04.310 --> 00:18:07.640 align:middle line:84%
everything took on this
brilliance, this energy,

00:18:07.640 --> 00:18:09.170 align:middle line:90%
this vitality, this glory.

00:18:09.170 --> 00:18:13.250 align:middle line:84%
Psychologically it was as if we
no longer had the psychic skin.

00:18:13.250 --> 00:18:15.500 align:middle line:84%
We had this deep
empathy with people.

00:18:15.500 --> 00:18:18.680 align:middle line:84%
Mystically, we saw our lives
as part of a much larger story.

00:18:18.680 --> 00:18:21.560 align:middle line:84%
And spiritually,
we knew ourselves

00:18:21.560 --> 00:18:24.350 align:middle line:90%
as God's seeds incarnate.

00:18:24.350 --> 00:18:26.160 align:middle line:90%
And that's what it's like.

00:18:26.160 --> 00:18:28.260 align:middle line:84%
It's an extraordinary
experience.

00:18:28.260 --> 00:18:33.920 align:middle line:84%
I think there is a return to the
mystic path in our time really.

00:18:33.920 --> 00:18:36.800 align:middle line:84%
Mysticism is the art
of union with reality.

00:18:36.800 --> 00:18:38.590 align:middle line:84%
And that's, of course,
what Jesus did.

00:18:38.590 --> 00:18:42.140 align:middle line:84%
And the mystic is one who really
realizes that that union is not

00:18:42.140 --> 00:18:44.990 align:middle line:90%
only possible, it's necessary.

00:18:44.990 --> 00:18:48.080 align:middle line:84%
How are we going to deal
with the immense complexities

00:18:48.080 --> 00:18:51.350 align:middle line:84%
of our time if we are
not also god-seeded,

00:18:51.350 --> 00:18:54.260 align:middle line:84%
god-partnered, and
are in a sense,

00:18:54.260 --> 00:18:56.540 align:middle line:84%
we are the partner of
this larger process.

00:18:56.540 --> 00:18:58.508 align:middle line:90%
We are agents of the process.

00:18:58.508 --> 00:19:00.050 align:middle line:84%
And when you look
at the mystic path,

00:19:00.050 --> 00:19:03.460 align:middle line:84%
it really is very close to
Jesus' path as we see it.

00:19:03.460 --> 00:19:05.450 align:middle line:84%
And I try to show
that in my book.

00:19:05.450 --> 00:19:07.340 align:middle line:90%
That you wake up.

00:19:07.340 --> 00:19:09.170 align:middle line:84%
That there is that
statement, aha.

00:19:09.170 --> 00:19:10.730 align:middle line:90%
Oh, yes!

00:19:10.730 --> 00:19:14.030 align:middle line:84%
And then there is that
sense often of uh oh,

00:19:14.030 --> 00:19:16.230 align:middle line:84%
I've got to do
something about it.

00:19:16.230 --> 00:19:17.360 align:middle line:90%
I've got to cleanse myself.

00:19:17.360 --> 00:19:19.165 align:middle line:84%
So we have the story
of Jesus wakening.

00:19:19.165 --> 00:19:20.540 align:middle line:84%
Then we have a
story of his going

00:19:20.540 --> 00:19:22.490 align:middle line:84%
into the desert
to cleanse himself

00:19:22.490 --> 00:19:25.850 align:middle line:84%
of old habits, old
traditions, old expectations.

00:19:25.850 --> 00:19:27.560 align:middle line:84%
The devil, you know,
is a projection

00:19:27.560 --> 00:19:29.900 align:middle line:84%
says, I'll give you the
cities of the world,

00:19:29.900 --> 00:19:32.670 align:middle line:84%
get thee behind me, Satan, my
kingdom is of another order.

00:19:32.670 --> 00:19:34.130 align:middle line:90%
So that's the release.

00:19:34.130 --> 00:19:37.070 align:middle line:84%
And then followed
by the ministry,

00:19:37.070 --> 00:19:42.080 align:middle line:84%
which is the state of
illumination, of visionary

00:19:42.080 --> 00:19:44.018 align:middle line:90%
seeing of the miraculous.

00:19:44.018 --> 00:19:45.560 align:middle line:84%
This is also part
of the mystic path.

00:19:45.560 --> 00:19:46.310 align:middle line:90%
>> Doing good in the world.

00:19:46.310 --> 00:19:47.810 align:middle line:90%
>> Doing good in the world.

00:19:47.810 --> 00:19:53.598 align:middle line:84%
And great happiness, all those
parties, great celebration.

00:19:53.598 --> 00:19:55.640 align:middle line:84%
And then, of course, what
goes up must come down,

00:19:55.640 --> 00:19:57.307 align:middle line:84%
and you have the dark
night of the soul.

00:19:57.307 --> 00:19:59.630 align:middle line:84%
Jesus, of course, the
story and gets him and he--

00:19:59.630 --> 00:20:01.610 align:middle line:84%
And then, of course,
the crucifixion.

00:20:01.610 --> 00:20:04.020 align:middle line:84%
And then the final stage
is unification, union.

00:20:04.020 --> 00:20:04.820 align:middle line:90%
>> And there's.

00:20:04.820 --> 00:20:05.720 align:middle line:90%
>> Resurrection.

00:20:05.720 --> 00:20:08.450 align:middle line:84%
And that's true of many of our
lives, of all of our lives.

00:20:08.450 --> 00:20:11.810 align:middle line:84%
>> There seems to be a
paradox in this life.

00:20:11.810 --> 00:20:17.090 align:middle line:84%
That he who was crucified, who
met so much opposition, who

00:20:17.090 --> 00:20:19.520 align:middle line:84%
was an outsider of
the established order

00:20:19.520 --> 00:20:24.560 align:middle line:84%
has now become in many ways,
the symbol of mainstream

00:20:24.560 --> 00:20:26.690 align:middle line:84%
established
religious traditions.

00:20:26.690 --> 00:20:28.880 align:middle line:84%
>> I think he'd be
quite astonished.

00:20:28.880 --> 00:20:30.602 align:middle line:84%
I often thought
that if Jesus could

00:20:30.602 --> 00:20:32.060 align:middle line:84%
see what was done
in his name, he'd

00:20:32.060 --> 00:20:35.190 align:middle line:84%
have gone back into
the carpenter's shop

00:20:35.190 --> 00:20:36.440 align:middle line:90%
and would not have come out.

00:20:36.440 --> 00:20:39.260 align:middle line:90%
But that's probably not true.

00:20:39.260 --> 00:20:46.290 align:middle line:84%
Yes, things begin in, in
so many different things.

00:20:46.290 --> 00:20:47.850 align:middle line:90%
You have the primary revelation.

00:20:47.850 --> 00:20:50.918 align:middle line:84%
You have the one who has
the fullness of spirit.

00:20:50.918 --> 00:20:53.460 align:middle line:84%
And then you have the second
and third and fourth generation,

00:20:53.460 --> 00:20:54.630 align:middle line:90%
and there's a diminution.

00:20:54.630 --> 00:20:56.190 align:middle line:90%
And then an occasional genius.

00:20:56.190 --> 00:21:00.020 align:middle line:84%
But that's true of anything and
anybody and any institution.

00:21:00.020 --> 00:21:01.440 align:middle line:90%
>> The things get crystallized.

00:21:01.440 --> 00:21:03.630 align:middle line:84%
>> They get crystallized,
they get encapsulated,

00:21:03.630 --> 00:21:04.470 align:middle line:90%
they get stuck.

00:21:04.470 --> 00:21:09.030 align:middle line:84%
And people settle for mediocrity
and not the radical demand.

00:21:09.030 --> 00:21:11.040 align:middle line:84%
The problem with Jesus
is his radical demand.

00:21:11.040 --> 00:21:11.840 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:21:11.840 --> 00:21:13.920 align:middle line:84%
>> These things I
do, you shall do,

00:21:13.920 --> 00:21:17.880 align:middle line:84%
you are a son and daughter of
God, and better live as such.

00:21:17.880 --> 00:21:22.500 align:middle line:84%
>> So even as sort of a
mainstream religious icon,

00:21:22.500 --> 00:21:26.377 align:middle line:84%
he's calling people to
something revolutionary.

00:21:26.377 --> 00:21:27.210 align:middle line:90%
>> And evolutionary.

00:21:27.210 --> 00:21:29.410 align:middle line:90%
Not simply revolutionary.

00:21:29.410 --> 00:21:35.310 align:middle line:84%
He's calling us to the unfolding
of our primary condition, which

00:21:35.310 --> 00:21:41.040 align:middle line:84%
is stewards of revolution,
stewards of the taking

00:21:41.040 --> 00:21:42.390 align:middle line:90%
care of the planet.

00:21:42.390 --> 00:21:44.730 align:middle line:84%
I mean, what would happen
to this planet, Jeffrey,

00:21:44.730 --> 00:21:46.110 align:middle line:90%
if we all became Christic?

00:21:46.110 --> 00:21:47.920 align:middle line:84%
How would we then
be able to see?

00:21:47.920 --> 00:21:50.400 align:middle line:84%
I mean he who looked
so closely at nature

00:21:50.400 --> 00:21:53.040 align:middle line:84%
and used all these natural
images, consider the birds,

00:21:53.040 --> 00:21:57.900 align:middle line:84%
consider the lilies, neither
do they, they don't sow,

00:21:57.900 --> 00:22:00.060 align:middle line:84%
they don't reap, and yet
Solomon all his glory

00:22:00.060 --> 00:22:03.120 align:middle line:84%
and array as these, they
just hang out and are happy.

00:22:03.120 --> 00:22:04.210 align:middle line:90%
What would it be like?

00:22:04.210 --> 00:22:06.720 align:middle line:84%
How would we take the
Christic attitude, that deep

00:22:06.720 --> 00:22:08.742 align:middle line:90%
compassionate caring, evoke it?

00:22:08.742 --> 00:22:10.200 align:middle line:84%
>> It sounds like
we might be less.

00:22:10.200 --> 00:22:11.283 align:middle line:90%
>> We'd be very different.

00:22:11.283 --> 00:22:14.760 align:middle line:84%
>> Concerned with our material
welfare and more concerned with

00:22:14.760 --> 00:22:15.645 align:middle line:90%
healing the planet.

00:22:15.645 --> 00:22:18.270 align:middle line:84%
>> The treasures in heaven, the
treasures in the depths of what

00:22:18.270 --> 00:22:19.070 align:middle line:90%
we are.

00:22:19.070 --> 00:22:20.550 align:middle line:84%
And from the depths
of what, I've

00:22:20.550 --> 00:22:23.250 align:middle line:84%
spent a lifetime looking
at the treasures within.

00:22:23.250 --> 00:22:27.210 align:middle line:84%
And I assure you, if we began
to use just a tiny percentage

00:22:27.210 --> 00:22:29.940 align:middle line:84%
of the capacities that we have
and the knowledge that all

00:22:29.940 --> 00:22:32.160 align:middle line:84%
of us have, this would be
a very different planet

00:22:32.160 --> 00:22:34.160 align:middle line:90%
within 20 years.

00:22:34.160 --> 00:22:35.820 align:middle line:90%
>> And we have that possibility.

00:22:35.820 --> 00:22:37.450 align:middle line:84%
>> We certainly
do, and we have to.

00:22:37.450 --> 00:22:38.800 align:middle line:90%
We've run out of time.

00:22:38.800 --> 00:22:39.630 align:middle line:90%
We have to use it.

00:22:39.630 --> 00:22:43.020 align:middle line:84%
We have to become what we
are, the possible human who

00:22:43.020 --> 00:22:44.580 align:middle line:90%
creates the possible society.

00:22:44.580 --> 00:22:47.230 align:middle line:84%
>> Jean Houston, we
have run out of time.

00:22:47.230 --> 00:22:49.320 align:middle line:84%
But it's such a
joy to be with you

00:22:49.320 --> 00:22:53.280 align:middle line:84%
and to have this sense of our
own inner greatness reawakened

00:22:53.280 --> 00:22:54.895 align:middle line:90%
through this conversation.

00:22:54.895 --> 00:22:56.520 align:middle line:84%
Jean, thanks so much
for being with me.

00:22:56.520 --> 00:22:58.060 align:middle line:84%
>> Thank you,
Jeffrey, thank you.

00:22:58.060 --> 00:23:00.050 align:middle line:90%
>> It's been a pleasure.

00:23:00.050 --> 00:23:03.340 align:middle line:90%
